# Frontend Conventions — GoClaw WebUI

## Stack

- React 18+ with TypeScript
- Vite for bundling
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- SSE (Server-Sent Events) for real-time streaming

## Directory Structure

- `web/src/pages/` — page components (Chat, Dashboard, Sessions, etc.)
- `web/src/components/` — shared UI components
- `web/src/layouts/` — layout wrappers (AppLayout, SetupLayout)
- `web/src/hooks/` — custom React hooks (useChat, etc.)
- `web/src/lib/` — utilities (api.ts, sse.ts, utils.ts)

## SSE Streaming

- Use `createPOSTSSEConnection` for unified send+stream (POST-based SSE)
- Use `createSSEConnection` for legacy GET-based SSE
- Handle events: `delta`, `tool_use`, `done`, `error`, `run_start`

## Patterns

- Use TypeScript strict mode
- Use functional components with hooks
- Colocate types near usage
- API calls go through `web/src/lib/api.ts`

## Do NOT

- Create test files unless explicitly requested
- Create documentation files unless explicitly requested
